  "signature": "ed25519:afd0290ccbfd2001f523be65f8ab21c7700e81dfd4916baf5289ae79bafa7d3b8955623fd767d3a3a8d95f357a5d8b044d567c9c48954996f3b899884ebbee0b",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R1) is a commercially validated, FDA-recognized software tool. Version control, change management, and regression testing records are maintained. Software quality assurance documentation satisfies MRL 2 requirements for a Class II device at Medium assurance level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification was performed using the method of manufactured solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the power-law hemolysis model. Observed convergence rates match theoretical order of accuracy (second-order spatial, first-order temporal). Benchmark suite results for internal flow problems are consistent with published literature. Achieved level 3 exceeds MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl2",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed following ASME V&V 20 guidelines. Grid convergence index (GCI) for the hemolysis index quantity of interest was computed as 3.8%, within the 5% threshold for MRL 2. Richardson extrapolation confirmed asymptotic convergence. The production mesh (6.2M hexahedral cells) was selected based on GCI analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions are documented in detail including blood analog fluid properties (glycerol-water mixture, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s at 37°C), pump rotational speeds (2400–3600 RPM), and flow rates (2–6 L/min). Temperature, inlet pressure, and outlet back-pressure were controlled and recorded throughout testing. Calibration records for all instrumentation are available and traceable to NIST standards."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2",
      "rationale": "CFD predictions for relative hemolysis index, pressure head, and flow-speed characteristic curves were compared quantitatively against experimental measurements. Statistical metrics include mean absolute error, root-mean-square error, and 95% confidence intervals. All primary quantities of interest fall within acceptance tolerances defined in the credibility plan. Graphical and tabular comparisons are documented in the V&V report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest — relative hemolysis index (RH) — is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1.0) and clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis. Secondary QoIs (pressure head, shear stress distribution) are mechanistically connected to hemolysis prediction. A traceability matrix maps each QoI to the COU decision question and the predicate device comparison basis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under operating conditions (flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid properties) that span and bracket the COU operating envelope. The validation domain overlaps with the prediction domain for all five operating points evaluated in the COU. Differences between validation and prediction conditions are documented and their impact on model credibility is assessed as negligible for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error is scoped out at MRL 2 for this Class II device assessment. The commercial solver (ANSYS Fluent) employs double-precision arithmetic; floating-point round-off errors are orders of magnitude below discretization error contributions. Iterative convergence is monitored via residual norms (< 1e-6 for all equations) and mass balance checks (< 0.01%). No additional solver error quantification is required at this model risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is scoped out at MRL 2. The simulation was executed by a credentialed CFD analyst with documented training on the solver and hemolysis modeling protocols. An independent peer review of simulation setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing was completed prior to result acceptance. Documented simulation execution checklist is on file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty assessment is scoped out at MRL 2 for this COU. The RANS k-omega SST turbulence model is the established standard for internal cardiovascular device flows and has been validated extensively in the FDA benchmark program. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) is the accepted formulation for device-induced hemolysis prediction. Alternative model forms are not required at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty quantification is scoped out at MRL 2. Key input parameters (fluid viscosity, density, pump geometry, boundary conditions) are well-characterized from experimental measurements with low uncertainty (< 2% for fluid properties, < 0.5% for geometric dimensions from CMM measurements). Sensitivity analysis confirmed that input uncertainties contribute less than 5% to output uncertainty, acceptable at this model risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Test sample characterization beyond standard material certification is scoped out at MRL 2. Blood analog fluid was prepared per ASTM F1841 protocol with certified glycerol and distilled water. Pump hardware used for validation testing was manufactured to drawing tolerances and dimensionally verified. No additional sample-to-sample variability characterization is required at this model risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equivalency-inputs-scopeout",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency analysis of input parameters between validation and prediction scenarios is scoped out at MRL 2. A qualitative mapping of validation test conditions to COU operating conditions has been performed and documented, confirming that the validation envelope encompasses the prediction domain. Dimensional analysis confirms dynamic similarity is maintained across the operating range evaluated."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv40-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the CFD hemolysis prediction model supporting the CPB use case is accepted at Medium assurance level for Model Risk Level 2. All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels: software quality assurance (2/2), numerical code verification (3/2, exceeds requirement), discretization error (2/2), test conditions (2/2), output comparison (2/2), relevance of quantities of interest (2/2), and relevance of validation activities to COU (2/2). The six remaining factors (numerical solver error, use error, model form, model inputs, test samples, equivalency of input parameters) are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented rationale for each. Validation results demonstrate that CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index, pressure head, and velocity field are in quantitative agreement with experimental measurements across the full COU operating envelope. The maximum predicted RH = 0.87 satisfies the RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion with adequate margin. Uncertainty quantification has been completed for all three validation results, and the provenance chain from raw experimental data through simulation activities to final validation results is fully documented. The structured evidence base, completeness of factor assessment, and quantitative agreement between predictions and measurements collectively support acceptance of this model for the stated context of use.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
